Description: Floor sherd of South Ionian pottery open vessel, possibly a plate; interior: wide black band with narrow added red band superimposed; tondo reserved save for central black circle; exterior: trace of black foot remaining; on underside six dilute bands outside glaze dot and two circles; inscription on underside.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GE.907)
